Review: Shrimp tacos! Really nice outdoor vibe in Oakland. Shrimp tacos were pretty good.
Very good upscale restaurant in Oakland. The brussel sprouts and garlic bread were phenomenal. Got the Branzino fish plate which was also very good - just a little boney.
Chowda so good!
Always a 5. Standard order of arincini ball, boom pie (basil, tomato, ricotta, garlic), and Bianca. Boom pie is phenomenal, Bianca not bad but wouldn‚Äôt order again.
Got tie dye pizza! Strong four but wouldn‚Äôt crave like John‚Äôs boom pie.
Brussel sprouts, steak, mac and cheese. Grad dinner for Neena. Nice ambiance but food was ok.

Shared lots of dishes with large group including arincini balls, different pasta, pizza, lasagna, and dessert. Best dishes were the arincini, lasagna, and chocolate pie. Crazy good despite being vegan - very nice ambiance.
Very tasty burrito. I went here once a week for my vegan meal. Accessible because it was close to where I lived.
Nice ambiance, upscale, Indian food is modern and decent. However I‚Äôve had better and it‚Äôs a bit pricey.
Japanese fried chicken. My favorite spot in Oakland - fried chicken so good with excellent glazed sauce. Always try to go back when I‚Äôm in town.
Surprisingly very solid fast food chicken fingers. Got it with mustard, sweet bbq, and lemon piccata sauce. Incredible when you combine them together.

Known for South Indian food (see previous review)! Got North Indian this time and it was only ok. Split malai kofta and paneer. Not bad but not great - wasn‚Äôt super creamy pretty clean. Wouldn‚Äôt come back for North Indian food here.
Surprisingly good pancakes - pretty fluffy. That being said I only had 3 unlike @pranav who had 16 üòÇüòÇüòÇ
Strong 3. Egg skillet was pretty good but pancakes were ok (no chocolate thanks sakthi üò°) and potatoes were actually not great.
Good drunk food pizza - very cheesy

Best restaurant I‚Äôve been to in NYC. They have this incredible concept where they invite grandmothers from around the world to cook homemade meals. The menu changes every day depending who‚Äôs in the kitchen. 

Yesterday we had an excellent 4 course meal. Started with a full harvest salad that was light but fruity. Then got two entrees - Turkish rabbit and Italian Domenica pasta. The rabbit was very tender and tasted very good (something I have never had before) but the Domenica pasta was some of best Italian food I have ever had. The pasta had insane amount of tomato sauce and the complimentary meat just melted in your mouth.

For dessert we got homemade gelato which was excellent as well. 

I am excited to go back and try the next thing on their menu (and don‚Äôt worry @sakthi lots of vegetarian options too)!
Trip chocolate cookie dough ice cream. Tasty but way too heavy, only ate 20%
Decent gnocchi and wine in east village. Wouldn‚Äôt crave but not bad.
Pretty good thin crust pizza spot. Went with the cousins and got a bunch of meat pizzas including an excellent red mozzarella, onion and bacon pizza.
Best place to watch a game in the city. Good bar food as well but go for the viewing experience.
Souvla pizza - pretty good and close to Oakland office
Split the sweet potato burrito and mushroom taco. Burrito is 5, tacos are also super solid.
Seeing @pratik made me crave a burger. Got a standard burger from the place - was not bad but nothing special.

Went around midnight and they were out of most flavors. Got the earl grey tea ice cream which was ok. I did go once before and remember it being good so will try again when most flavors are on the menu.
Favorite NYC restaurant. Got the bread, butternut squash ravioli and cookies. So damn good. See previous post for pics.
Really solid! See why it‚Äôs beloved in Boston
Punch cocktail, trout, fries, cheesecake and sticky toffee cake. Pretty good food, nice ambiance. Super expensive.
Actual NYC hole in the wall - took 5 min to find, excellent fried goat cheese, yum chocolate cake, bartender made us custom drinks, super nice ambiance
Got crispy chicken sandwich and fries. Decent food but giving a 4 since it was a spacious bars with lots of TVs for US Open. Great place to watch a classic Alcaraz 5 setter.
Got the chaat platter!! The dahi and bhel chaat were pretty good! Corn was a bit spicy. Wouldn‚Äôt crave but thought it was solid.
Malai kofta, paneer tikka, aloo chaat. Super good east village indian. That being said it‚Äôs not something I would crave.
Got the egg, cheese, and spinach bagel (called Murray the cop and replaced red pepper with spinach). So good - best NYC bagel yet.
Pineapple fried rice. Pretty good and can make last minute reservations.
Super tasty burger and truffle fries. The fries were really really good.

Very strong 4! Great Indian food in Costa Rica. Chicken kebabs, lamb korma, and garlic naan all 5s. The paneer tikka, butter chicken, and malai kofta all also very good. Super nice service. Not sure if I would crave but definitely would go again.
Very good bagel spot. Got sesame bagel, egg, hash brown in the bagel. Was pretty heavy and pretty good but I do think Tompkins is better.

Place: Lolita Cocina & Tequila Bar Fort Point
Review: Really good corn bread and super cheesy quesadilla. Nice ambiance.
Really good Artisan pizza in Cambridge. Really liked the squash prosciutto pizza.
Decent burrito, California ones are better
Really nice ambiance. More of an upscale place for date nights and celebrations.
Could have been so good it wasn‚Äôt for an ungodly amount of spice. Couldn‚Äôt finish the curry - too spicy. Surprised at the spice level given the amount of non Indians there.
Incredible fried chicken in Oakland. Went all the time at my old job - always crave when I come back. Get with their famed miso sauce!!
Go to SF brunch spot. Millionaire bacon sampler, California burger and Thai ice tea. 30 min wait but super worth - highly recommend whenever in SF.
An NYC staple. So heavy but so good. Got pastrami sandwich and matza ball soup.
Excellent lobster ravioli - really lively ambiance in downtown Boston
Got pesto green machine pizza and pepperoni pizza. Pesto green machine was good - nice ricotta cheese. Pepperoni was really good but I wouldn‚Äôt crave it.
Solid rooftop bar in San Jose Costa Rica. The bean dip and empanadas were very very good. The burger was ok - a little charred. Tried a bite of churro which was also pretty good.
Excellent late night pizza in North Boston
Fried chicken sandwich and fries! Really good fried chicken sandwich - coworkers love this place. That being said I like Aburaya better.
Chicken burrito. Solid but nothing special.
Got a slew of decent apps (fried cheese balls were the best!) and a mushroom/ricotta cheese pizza. Very very good but would not crave. Really nice outdoor vibe.
Solid fried chicken place. Beef dumplings were really good, super tender. Scallion pancakes also very good. Note - the original means no sauce, get sauce for the chicken.
Very good Columbus based cafe. Chocolate crossaint very moist and the egg sandwich is a strong 4/weak 5. Almost a weak 5.
Grilled cheese is so good, cookie shot super unique, dka and almond croissant also fire. Great ambiance.
Great location, good chicken quesadilla
Really good seafood place. Mussels were super tender, snapper was good but too many bones, mahi-mahi was delicious!
Solid Korean brunch place close to the Marina. The millionaire bacon was superb and the pork belly bibimbap was solid.
Ah this a 5! Not a 4.
Really fluffy, good cheese to bread ratio. Definitely heavier and more of a date night once in awhile thing. Best pizza in the city.
Nice bar in east village! Got the chips and guac and queso. Ordered a margarita drink. Decent drinks/food - nice vibe.
Solid pizza spot in New Albany. My go to when I‚Äôm home.
Amazing Indian Italian blend of pizza with paneer. Great drink food. I eat it once in awhile though because it‚Äôs a bit unhealthy.

Strong 4 - went after a night of going out with @sakthi. Split the malai kofta and malai paneer. Really good and very very creamy - just didn‚Äôt sit super well after drinking. Will want to try again more sober.
Eggplant parmigiana was so good, tie die pizza was hands down amazing (thins crust), the white pizza was ok probably would not get again

Amazing sandwich spot in Williamsburg. Got the breakfast sandwich which includes sharp white cheddar, tomato, egg, house made bacon jam, horse radish creme fraiche and arugula served pressed on buttered sourdough.

Got white square pizza and grandma (red) pizza. SO GOOD! Best pizza in NY so far. Grandma was solid - marinara sauce very good. The white pizza was insane. Great mix of cheese - ricotta was so good. Will definitely be coming back!!!
Overhyped. Only memorable part is that we had to leave early because someone got a little too tipsy on vday üòÇ

Great views of ferry building and bay bridge (the better SF bridge imo). Got the spicy mango drink which was pretty good and a good number of apps. Lamb sliders were tender and Mediterranean bread plate was solid.
Falafel sandwich and fries. Falafel sandwich was ok but way too salty. Fries were good but sandwich made this a 3. Probably won‚Äôt go back.
Solid spot, close to apt

Place: Mr. B‚Äôs BBQ with a kick
Review: Solid southern barbecue food on the way to Pensacola. Insane portion sizes and felt incredibly full after. Got pulled pork, brisket, mac and cheese, cornbread, and garlic bread.

Insane new american food in Hudson Square. Got the house rolls and kale pita to start. Kale pita was ok but the house rolls were phenomenal. Then for the mains we split the pasta pomodoro and honeynut squash ravioli. Pomodoro was good but the ravioli was to die for. It was soo good we almost ordered another üòÖ. Finally for dessert got the chocolate chip cookies which honestly might be the best cookies I‚Äôve ever had. So small, soft, and delicious. Will be craving them for sure. Outside area a little quiet/boring but inside was nice.
Underrated gem in SF - ty to @chan for finding. Bear batter ice cream. Speciality of baked bear. Basically cookies and ice cream.
Good bagel place. Got a really good savory egg bagel sandwich. Sweet bagel was ok but had to split with sakthi so no chocolate. Would go back to try chocolate but not something I would crave.
A+ bar to watch USA Netherlands match.
Nice place in downtown Danville. Really nice bread, brussel sprouts, salad appetizer. Pork chops super tender. Nice ambiance and vibe.
Got two scoop stracciatella and chocolate. Looks nice but chocolate was too heavy. I threw half of it away.
Got Ôøºa sweet Lambrusco half bottle with @sakthi as well as cheese plate. Cheese was mediocre and wine was ok but giving a 4 since the ambiance is nice.
This pizza slaps üòÇ @tyler . Solid drunchies food in Columbus.
An Ann Arbor staple. Made my own sandwich and it was incredible. Must go when in town.

Went with coworkers for dinner! Really good Japanese fusion restaurant in Oakland. Split a bunch of appetizers and got the black garlic oil Tonkotsu. Really liked the pork belly and has a nice indoor vibe.

Excellent food close to apt. Shared a hummus plate, eggplant dip, and lamb shanks. Hummus was great, eggplant dip got better as you kept on eating it. Lamb was super tender. Will definitely be going back.
Really good upscale Mexican food - loved their cheese dip, tacos, fajita, and churro. Lively ambiance during the weekend. Would take people from out of town.
Decent paneer, have had better

Really solid brunch spot! High 4 for sure. Split the egg and cheese bagel and ricotta french toast. Bags was pretty good but Tompkins is better. French toast melted in your mouth - so good. Got the cream cheese boreka - also super good. High 4 because I don‚Äôt think I would crave it like @sakthi but still super solid and would recommend.
Really good vegan sushi. You wouldn‚Äôt think it‚Äôs good but it‚Äôs super tasty. I always bring people from out of town here.
Overrated and overhyped. Super salty and not very tasty. Especially did not like cacio e pepe.
Good to be back. The best.

Gnocchi bites appetizer was good and super unique. Usually don‚Äôt like pesto pizza but this was absolutely phenomenal - great blend of pesto and balsamic. Sicilian pizza was also very good and fluffy. Had a nice cr√®me br√ªl√©e like dessert. Will definitely come back when I‚Äôm in NJ.
A classic Ohio staple. Brambleberry crisp and gooey butter cake. The best.
Snickdoodle and rainbow blondie. Super good - right off broadway. Snickerdoodle even better warmed up. Where the stars go to eat too!
Excellent bagel spot in east village. Will be my go to bagel spot.
Solid Indian place. Split the bhel chaat and dahi puri. Dahi puri was so good we ordered another! Also got the butter paper dosa which was really good but a little too thin for my liking.
Every time it hits the spot. Good to be back.
Decent cannoli - mikes was better
Got 10 honey bbq wings and fries with ranch. Food was solid but super heavy. Went to watch first half of Celtics game - place inside was a bit small. I wouldn‚Äôt crave but be down to come back.

Despite being so close I haven‚Äôt gone that often. Got the chicken pita wrap and pita/hummus. Was actually absolute fire and it‚Äôs going to be my relatively healthy option from now on. Went with @shaan @kartik @sid

Ok this is the actual place. Had amazing Doordash reviews but was bad delivered. Pav bhaji was ok a little spicy but not terrible. The butter chicken (the number one most popular on Doordash) was horrible. Super watery and had no flavor. Avoid this place (at least for delivery)!
Thai ice tea, pad thai, fried chicken, crab fried rice all shared. Went with a group. Nice ambiance but unfortunately a little too spicy.
It was ok. Got a make my own salad with sweet potato, beets, chicken, goat cheese, dressing etc. Too much lettuce and not enough other food. Mixt in SF is better and heartier.
Really good Japanese food! Really liked their sushi - especially their dragon roll.
Brooklyn blackout cupcake is phenomenal. Best cupcake.
Nice brunch spot in downtown Pensacola. Got the breakfast sandwich and fries. Nothing to hit home about but nice ambiance.
Again pictures didn‚Äôt attach smh
Best Indian spot in SF. It‚Äôs a hidden gem in Bernal heights and I take all my Indian friends there.
KFC in India >>>>> KFC in US. I crave the Zinger burger every single time I come here. Also costs $2 which is a nice plus.

Very very strong 4. Got the chicken appetizer (that lights on fire üî•), paneer sirka pyaaz, and tried @priya butternut squash kofta. All were super good (esp the kofta) but giving a 4 since it was a little too spicy. Will definitely go back and try it more mild.

Same taste & menu as the SF restaurant pre covid. Got the standard order of dahi puri chaat, aloo tiki chaat, paneer tikka, saag paneer, chole, and garlic naan. 

Both appetizers are fire but I love the dahi puri chaat. Mains also super good but loved loved the paneer tikka. I‚Äôve heard SF Tilak went down in quality so I wonder if the head chef moved here since this place was üî•üî•üî•
Went with @gita. Decent sushi spot - all full rolls. Really liked the scallop and yellowtail. Not super pricey given the amount of food.
California chicken burrito. It was ok, probably the best burrito in NY but honestly nothing to brag about. Chipotle is better.

Solid brunch spot! Went with @sakthi @ani @gita @sagar @jenny. Really nice vibe in Hell‚Äôs Kitchen. Good music in the background. Burger was good but a little over cooked. French toast sticks were fire.
Nice squash pizza, a little too crowded to hear other people

Very very solid - weak 5. Got the leek foccia bread which was incredible and the arincini balls which were also great. The mafaldini pasta was ok but the sheeps milk agnolotti pasta was also mouth watering. That being said given price and amount of time to get a reservation (months in advance) I would still recommend Lidens.
Chicken sandwich with fries. Cheap, filling, healthy. Always an SF staple. Baklava yogurt hits the spot on a nice day.
Good Thai place close to where I lived. Would go after playing Spikeball or going on a bike ride.
Best pizza in NYC! Got the boom pie (roasted tomato, ricotta, mozzarella) this time in addition to the classic cheese and calzone. All were straight fire and calzones was much better then last time.
Insane vegan Mexican food in east village. Split the mushroom tacos and sweet potato burrito. Both tasted super good and felt really clean. S/O to @gita for the rec.
CAVEAT - I got it delivered and only got soup dumplings and scallion pancakes. Scallion pancakes were ok and soup dumplings were good! I want to try again in person.
Good taco spot in Oakland! Chicken taco too spicy loool

OK CAVEAT. I got Liberty Bagels on Sunday on my way go NJ. Didn‚Äôt eat it fresh and had to wait for an hour or so. Got a sesame bagel with lettuce, tomato, avocado, and onion. Also got the rainbow bagel with walnut cream cheese. Bagels were ok but a bit stale. Cream cheese was ok but nothing special. Will try again fresh but I think Thompkins will still be my go to.

Pretty decent pasta! Got the eggplant parm appetizer which was mediocre and the rigatoni pasta @sakthi got was just ok. The pear and gorgonzola ravioli I got was actually pretty good. The real winner was we got two pitchers of margaritas for $18 (they forgot to charge us for one)!
Took @ani and converted him with the white pizza. Whipped ricotta and fluffy dough. Still best pizza in NY so far. See pics of Ani being basic af.
Always the best. Boom pie for life.
Phenomenal French toast and skillet is to die far, excellent ambiance

Crowd sourced this place from @ani @gita @john @pranav @sid. Unfortunately was not as good as advertised! Pork dumplings were ok - Hibachi is better. Scallion pancakes too dry. House noodles were fire though and honestly the only reason this place is a 4.

Really solid vegan asian place. Split the scallion pancakes and I think the king oyster mushrooms? Scallion pancakes were super solid! Got the kimchee fried rice which was super good! Would recommend especially for vegan and vegetarian.
Got takeout, nice drunk food, ambiance did look nice when we went to pick up
Great salad and sandwich spot in Berkeley. Got the BLTA sandwich. Massive portion sizes but still pretty healthy.
Good food but way too loud for a Sunday night
Very good Korean BBQ but had better in the bay, nice ambiance
Really good! Got a MASSIVE pita with chicken, saffron rice, taziki sauce, olives, beets, feta cheese, tomato, and dressing. Needed to warm it up since I took it to go but will go back.

Absolutely 5 star. Got the spicy guac to share (which actually wasn‚Äôt too spicy), fish tacos, and tres leches cake for dessert. The guac was pretty good, the tacos were absolutely fire, and the cake was really good and not too dry. Ambiance also super cute. One of the best Mexican places in NYC.
Really nice brunch spot in east village. Known for their burgers which were very tender. Fries also pretty crispy. French toast also solid. Would definitely be down to come back.
White pizza. The goat of pizzas besides a John‚Äôs. Everyone must try it.

Got bruschetta and meat lasagna flight. Bruschetta was ok, meat lasagna flight was good! Sakthis veggie one was better though haha. Ambiance ok - lady at the table next to us was drunk and yelling so couldn‚Äôt hear much
Ordered pickup, not great taste and a bit cold but could be better in person
Supposedly the best tacos in NY. Got the Al pastor, carne asada, and pollo tacos. Not bad but not great. California tacos are much better.
Got the Beca! A mix of egg, bacon, cheddar, avocado mash. Great bagel but I like Thompkins better.
Boom pie. Best pizza. 10/10. Tomatoes, garlic, ricotta, basil.
Really solid seafood place in short north. We shared the shishito peppers and I got the swordfish. Swordfish was really tender and incredibly flavorful. Also very nice upscale ambiance.
New Indian place in the mission. Mix of north and South Indian food. Split a masala dosa and chicken tikka dish. Food was very good - but nothing that would make me crave it.
Really nice ambiance and a great $50 deal for appetizer, main course, and dessert. Went with @shaan @kartik - got steak, lamb meatballs, flat bread, and sticky toffee pudding dessert.

Came here for @sid‚Äôs birthday. Solid Detroit styled pizza - really liked the VIP pizza (vodka sauce, red sauce, parsley pesto, pepperoni). Awesome bartender that gave everyone AMFs and took two shots with Sid.
Very good thin crust pizza rec from @kartik. Really liked plain and olives pizza.

Really good - a weak 5. Shared with @akhil - got the chicken and chili sauce (which was too spicy for me surprise surprise). Also got the Dan Dan noodles which were super solid. Got the soup pork dumplings which were incredible and the Peking duck which was so tender. Definitely down to go back.

Michelin star KBBQ. We got the butchers feast which is four cuts of the chefs selection for $65 per person. The four cuts were delicious - each successively better than the last. We also got the paella which was good but a bit spicy. Ambiance was great too. I want to go back to try Omakase cuts which is more expensive ($185 per person) but could be worth.

I had quite an experience going to Adda. To be fair I was out all day and went on a 10k run that morning so I was severely dehydrated. So eating heavy Indian food and drinking wine wasn‚Äôt the best combo.

Got a mix of things including dahi puri, vegetable pakora, paneer, and malai kofta with garlic naan. The appetizers were distinctly average, and the paneer had no cream. The malai kofta was the best food but still not phenomenal. Everything was a little too spicy.

Unfortunately due to all the dehydration I had a less than stellar experience in the restaurant. When I tried the food again the next night it was better but not something I would come back for. Food was a bit too creamy and too spicy for a taste.

Excellent upscale restaurant in Costa Rica. Went for lunch with the family. The drink was a spiked version of the native Costa Rica fruit which was amazing. The chips came in a little devils container which was cool and tasted nice. The lamb was so damn good - one of the best lamb I‚Äôve had. Fish was also very good. Finally tried a small bite of dessert - pretty good as well. Would definitely go back for the drink, chips, and lamb.
Ok place. Cheese curds are overrated by @ani. Big TV but no sound for games. Nice cream ale beer.

Got again one more time with @sakthi. Got an everything bagel with olive pimento cream cheese and egg as well as rainbow bagel with birthday cake cream cheese. Better than last time - actually pretty flavorful and good bagel. But Thompkins is 100% better.
Really nice bbq place in Texas. Great outdoor vibes. Brisket was hella good, ribs ok, and sausage was not good.
Decent pizza, great sangria, nice ambiance
Got it delivered, pierogis were phenomenal, latkes were not great

Went for @umang birthday celebration. Got a whole slew of apps including hummus, baba ghanoush, spicy potatoes etc. Also got our own personal table chicken shawarma - insane amount of chicken, pita, and fries. Topped it off with a celebration chocolate lava cake. Great good - weak 5 only because the service was slow and not good.

Really solid food! Split the empanadas and arepa with a mix of meat and veggie. Also split the octopus paella and brisket/rice/beans. Empanadas and octopus were really good! Nice ambiance in Williamsburg.
Burger and fries. A classic.
Decent beef gyro but have had better, fries are ok, need to try chicken/lamb

Got an assortment of North and South Indian food including a couple of appetizers. Really liked the masala dosa, paneer tikka masala, and malai kofta. Would definitely want to come back when I am in NJ. Really solid comfort Indian food.
See Sakthis review

Really solid Indian food in kips bay. Dahi puri was pretty good, bhel puri was really good. Butter chicken was pretty good, super clean and not very oily. Also water was incredibly cold - was like it was from a glacier.
Family style with coworkers. Got a bunch of dishes but nothing spectacular. Best was probably the pad see-ew and the peanut sauce for the veggie rolls - everything else probably wouldn‚Äôt re-order.
Got aloo tikka chaat, chicken murgh kurma, malai kofta. Decent food, nice hole in the wall near Penn station, service was a little rude - they were trying to hurry us up
Really really good donut place! Brooklyn blackout was fire.

Insane Thai food! Went with @sakthi and @shaan parents. Split the appetizers chicken sautee, paratha, and tom ka soup. All fire especially the paratha. Then Ashish uncle and I split the chicken Thai curry and short rib Thai curry. Chicken was good, the short rib was incredible. So juicy and tender. Down to go back next time.
Very good bottomless and unlimited food in Dallas. Really liked the cheesy pita appetizers. Didn‚Äôt eat much of the pancakes üòÖ
Got white pizza and caprese pizza. Came on coworker recommendation. Honestly not super great. Pizza a little dry and things fell apart easily. Crust also not great.

Split a bunch of small dishes including labneh dip, stuffed pita, hummus, and frena bread. All good nothing great. Also split sweet potato, cauliflower, and fries. Loved the sweet potatoes, fries were just ok. Finally split apple cider sorbet which was excellent.
Really great breakfast sandwich and walnut coffee cake
Murray the cop is goat. Pesto, eggs, mozzarella, and roasted peppers.
Decent vegan Mediterranean food near MIT. Really liked the impossible meatball pita wrap.
Actually super fire I would say low 5. Got the cookies and cream with panna (whipped cream) which was super creamy and really chocolatey. It‚Äôs dangerous how close it is to my apt. Great rec @kartik
My go to cheap Chinese food/dumpling place. So good and so cheap. Probably a weekly staple now. If only Ani didn‚Äôt remove the favorites feature ‚òπÔ∏è
Super nice and well known in SF. Doesn‚Äôt have rice but still a great burrito. It‚Äôs my favorite burrito in the city.
Pics here! @ani let me edit.
Insanely good pizza. Stole some of Sakthis burrata since it was better than the margarita. Still think John‚Äôs and Village Sq is better but this is a close 3rd.
Decent sandwich nothing spectacular
California burrito, fried Oreos, not super good would not get again
Very good ice cream in Cambridge. Not Jenis/Salt and Straw level but still pretty good.
Also very fun ambiance, geeb dumplings were fire, rest of food great for sharing
Solid food! Got the burger and fries which were not bad but wouldn‚Äôt really crave.

Really solid seafood and steakhouse in Costa Rica. Split the ceviche, meatballs, and ribeye steak with dad and sister. Sampled the beet salad and cauliflower from mom. The ceviche was really good and the ribeye was pretty tender. The beet salad was also excellent. Really nice vibe in the center of La Fortuna. One of the better Costa Rican restaurant.
Super good dumplings and scallian pancakes for under $12. Really really filling
Insane portion sizes - everything meant to be shared. Literally 12 pieces of garlic bread, massive salad. Decent size ravioli and veal - all meant to share.
More of a go to place. Relatively healthy and light. It tastes so good, I eat there once a week. Accessible because multiple locations in the city.

The absolute goat of pizza. Got the combined corn and potato pizza. Been craving since I was here in July 2021. Not too oily, cheesy, or greasy. Just perfect.

Went with @sakthi @kruthi 

Hot take: Green sauce is a little overrated and spicy.
The absolute goat of fast food fried chicken. Will not let anyone ever tell me different. Get the Canes sauce it will change your life.
Got the classic Murray the Cop bagel. Pesto, eggs, roasted pepper, fresh mozzarella. 5 star.
Got the milk bar pie. Super sweet, really tasty, wouldn‚Äôt crave.
Strong 4, almost a 5! Really tasty seafood in Pensacola beach. Got the clam chowder, swordfish and shrimp risotto in brown butter. Wouldn‚Äôt crave it but always down to go back.

Decent food! I was starving due to insane workout day and chowed down on chips and guac. Got three tacos with fish, beef, and pork. Tacos were ok but nothing to brag about. Got a pitcher of magritas which was a bad idea given how dehydrated I was.
Burrata basil pizza. Decent but don‚Äôt understand the hype.
Recommendation from the boy @pratik. Got the Brooklyn blackout cupcake which was honestly one of the best cupcakes ever.
Had the breakfast sandwich and apple honey grilled cheese. Breakfast sandwich was really good with crossaint. Grilled cheese not bad but didn‚Äôt love aftertaste.
Solid deep dish spinach pizza in Danville. Reminds me of Zachary‚Äôs.
Really solid spot in Danville. Split pork chops and shrimp with Vik. Pork chops super tender. Great atmosphere.
Best pizza I‚Äôve had in New York. Classic cheese felt like it was straight from Italy. Not too heavy or cheesy. Calzone was good as well!
Original banana pudding with chocolate pieces. Pudding was not too sweet and hit nicely on a hot day.
Solid food - had low key night club vibes. Split a bunch of dishes to share but only really liked the Pad Thai and chicken fried rice.
Quintessential Philly cheesesteak. Pretty good, super heavy - only ate half! Wouldn‚Äôt crave but you got to try once. @shaan dad told me Gino‚Äôs is better so will try that next time.
Got a thin crust pizza. Pretty good. Ambiance was a bit loud - @gita couldn‚Äôt here us :(
Had Pastrami sandwich, fries, beer. Decent food, great atmosphere, definitely should go once.
My Saturday lunch spot when I lived in SF, really good sandwiches across the board, Charlie (owner) is super nice and great guy to talk to

Called restaurante fortuneno (couldn‚Äôt find) but really enjoyed this place! Two locations - go to the one downtown that only takes walks in because it‚Äôs more lively. We ran into another family we met on our hiking tour so we decided to eat with them! I got the ribs which were an absolute delicacy. 10/10 recommend going there.
Turkey and cranberry sandwich. Not great - would not go back.
A staple. Chicken sandwich garlic fries.
Got chips and guac and chicken enchilada. Solid food - strong 3/weak 4.
Really good spot in SF. Got pork gyozas, fried chicken, pork tacos, and lettuce wraps. Fried chicken was fire, the gyozas also really good. Down to come back for weekend bottomless brunch.

Such a vibe. Unlimited pizza - they just come around and offer. I had literally 20 slices! Great mix of regular pizzas and dessert pizzas. Dessert pizzas honestly better than regular.

Too damn spicy despite calling before and asking. Had the chaat app and dipped lmao. Nice waiting staff they didn‚Äôt charge up but I left a tip anyways.

Food from the county of Georgia! Got a mix of different appetizers - lots filled with cheese. First got the taste of Georgia - bread with a bunch of different spreads. Then got both the Adjaruli Khachapuri and Megurli Khachapuri. The Megurli looks like a little pizza but was incredibly fluffy - would definitely get in. Finally split the Kvari cheese dumplings. 

Strong 4 - the Megurli was definitely a 5. Thanks to @shaifali for the rec.
Hot vegan noodles and pork burger. Really solid Chinese food, but not something I would crave. Felt super clean too.
So so so good, close by to my apt in SF, really filling tortas
Best Indian food in NYC! Split the dahi chaat, channa, paneer tikka, malai kofta, and garlic naan. paneer and malai are so good - naan was incredibly fluffy.

Solid ramen place. Really liked the apps of pork bao and fried chicken. Original pork ramen was ok. Had a massive group so hard for waiters to get all the orders right.

Hardware store turned fancy brunch spot. Went with family. Split the cheeseboard appetizer, burgers and fries. Cookie is super soft and chocolatey - huge fan. Strong 4 as it is very good but would not crave.
